leawood.adapters.rest.Rest.doc: The Rest class is an implmenetation of the Repository abstract class to provide a REST implemenation of a persistence layer.

leawood.adapters.token.doc:
[header] operation=NODEINTRO serial_id=ABCD domain=power class=sensor name=solar [mdp bus_voltage] unit=volts symbol=V multiplier=1.0 [mdp load_current] unit=amps symbol=A multiplier=1.0

mdp Becomes a group name specific for a particular property. [mdp bus_voltage] defines the metadata specific for the bus_voltage property. This assumes that these definitions are not yet defined in the application. In the new model, it is assumed that the definitions are pre defined and standard so the bus_voltage metadata is can be already assumed. This means that the metadata model itself, just needs to connect the properties to the node.

[header] operation=NODEINTRO serial_id=ABCD domain=power class=sensor [properties] bus_voltage_v load_current_a

HEADER_GROUP operation serial_id domain class RS 10 11 06 12 xx xx xx xx xx xx xx xx 13 xx 14 xx PROPERTY_GROUP bus_voltage_v shunt_voltage_v load_current_ma 20 01 01 01

20 Bytes

In this case the name is no longer provided by the devices. This would be added later by the user from within the applications. The property names are suffixed with the unit and mulitplier to differentiate between similar properties with different multipliers.

[header] operation=DATA serial_id=ABCD [data] bus_voltage_v=10.5 load_current_a=3.6

HEADER_GROUP operation serial_id 01 01 03 01 01 DATA_GROUP value ... RS 01 01 04 ... 01

7 + 5xn bytes 3 properties = 7 + 5x3 = 22 bytes.

leawood.adapters.token.tokenise.doc: Parses the Telegram type and builds a bytearray of the elements so that this will be a reduced form for transmission.

leawood.adapters.token.detokenise.doc: Rehydrates a Telegrm from a byte array of tokens.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeTelegram.doc: The XBeeTelegram represents the message to be written to the XBee modem device. The __repr__ method is setup to output the payload to be passed down to the modem.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.doc: Provides the XBee implementation of a Modem.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.__init__.doc: The constructor for the XBeeModem object. This requires a config object to provide the correct configuration to be able to make a connection to the actual physical XBee modem module.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.send_mes.doc: Sends a message via the implemented modem to a device that is addressed within the message.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.register.doc: Registers the fuction to be called when the XBee module recevies a message. The message recevied from the XBee module will be of type XBeeMessage. This will be converted to Message and bassed to the callback.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.receive_.doc: The handler for the messages recevied by the XBee module. This function will parse the content of the XBeeMessage and convert this to a Message type and pass this to the callback.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.open.doc: Opens the connection to the XBee module.

leawood.adapters.xbee.XBeeModem.close.doc: Closes the connection to the XBee module.

leawood.adapters.xbee.create_telegram_fr.doc: A message needs to be converted to a XBeeTelegram type. This is the payload of the XBeeMessage to go out to the target device. The basic telegram contains a serial_id, an operation and a payload. The payload is a name value pair.
